OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBBC defends policy not to  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fcall Hamas 'terrorists'    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The BBC has defended its decision not  
OL,6, to describe Hamas militants as         
OL,7, "terrorists" in coverage of the recent 
OL,8, attacks in Israel.                     
OL,10,FUK Defence Secretary Grant Shapps said 
OL,11,Fthe policy is "verging on disgraceful".
OL,13,FA BBC spokesperson noted it was a      
OL,14,Flong-standing position for its         
OL,15,Freporters not to use the term          
OL,16,Fthemselves unless attributing it to    
OL,17,Fsomeone else.                          
OL,19,FVeteran BBC foreign correspondent John 
OL,20,FSimpson said "calling someone a        
OL,21,Fterrorist means you're taking sides".  
